class RecentCounter {

    private Deque<Integer> queue;

    public RecentCounter() {
        queue = new ArrayDeque<>();
    }

    public int ping(int t) {
        queue.add(t);
        while (!queue.isEmpty() && queue.peekFirst() < t - 3000) {
            queue.pollFirst();
        }
        return queue.size();
    }
}
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution uses a deque to store the timestamps of the requests. When a new request is added, it removes all the requests that are out of the time frame. This operation is done in O(n) time initially, but since the deque is updated after each request, the time complexity becomes O(1) on average. The space complexity is O(n) because in the worst case, all requests are stored in the deque.

